div.p: Bio: 🚀 CTO at TheGoodz | 🐍 Python & GraphQL enthusiast | 💼 Entrepreneur | ☁️ Google Cloud Platform advocate | 🌐 Serverless architecture explorer | 🎁 Open-source contributor

Tristen Harr is the Chief Technology Officer at TheGoodz, where he leads a small but mighty team of developers building innovative and elegant solutions for the industry's most pressing problems. With extensive experience in Python, GraphQL, entrepreneurship, Google Cloud Platform, and serverless architecture, Tristen is passionate about creating cool things and sharing his knowledge with others.

li.p: MyPyBuilder (Unmaintained) A tkinter wrapper that simplifies GUI creation with a drag-and-drop interface, enabling users to easily generate project folders with code files and stubbed-out commands.

api2db (Maintained, no new development) A versatile Python library designed for easy collection, processing, and storage of data from any API, with support for multiple storage targets and database types.

pysura (Maintained, active development) A revolutionary CLI tool for building and deploying multi-tenant enterprise-grade applications, Pysura combines the best of Hasura, Python, GraphQL, and Flutter. It provides a user-friendly command-line interface, serverless architecture, robust GraphQL integration, fine-tuned permissions, built-in authentication, and strong support for Flutter, enabling developers to create secure, scalable, and high-quality applications with ease.
Link: https://libraries.io/pypi/pysura Sponsoring the development of this library helps support its continued growth and improvement! 🌟
